Program: Outlook
Title: 04/07/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00tt7jv
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 5 Jul 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the British man who was moved between different care institutions and foster families 14 times during his childhood, but has managed to turn his life around. He's now a musician and actor and campaigns for the care system to be reformed to help other children in his position. Also, the paralysed Kenyan artist who paints by holding the brush in her mouth. And the pianist who is using music to bring together the young people of Iraq. The orchestra she founded is due to perform in Edinburgh this summer. Show less